DESCRIPTION: Typically one or two resources and up to six personnel assigned.
Several resources required.  Control typically achieved in one operational period.
Incident may extend into several operational periods. A Type 3 Team may be assigned.  A significant number of resources may be assigned.

Exceeds the local control capability.  May require non-local resources to manage incident.  Most Command and General Staff positions are filled.  A written IAP is required.  Operations personnel usually do not exceed 200 per operational period.

Highest complexity incident, requiring national resources to manage incident.  All Command and General Staff positions activated.  Operations personnel exceeds 500 per operational period.  High impact to local jurisdiction.
